document_data.History:
Trifakas had arrived together with Pawnis and Sardok about one week before the adventurers who ultimately resurrected [[Martek]] did. The two thieves were the last of Trifakas' band. The three discovered they were trapped soon after entering;{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|108}} Trifakas decided to live in a hut with Sardok, away from the Guilders.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|116}} When new adventurers came bearing every [[Star gem of Martek]], he had both thieves investigate these new arrivals,{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|109}} along with the local villagemaster [[Bandik]].{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|115}}

He may have personally spoken with those adventurers. If so, he wanted to know if they had any large gems, telling them that to his knowledge, that was the only way out of the garden. He may have sent Sardok to filch all the Star Gems of Martek from the adventurers and used them to open the doors of Grandal himself.

If Trifakas' band managed to acquire the Star Gems, they may have proceeded with the trials of Martek.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|111}} In such a case, they may have been found dead by the entrance of Martek's treasury.{{cite book/Desert of Desolation|126}}
